{"comments":"FPS — Frames per second atom for animation and video timing.\n\nRepresents the rate at which frames are displayed or processed.\nUsed in motion graphics, video editing, game loops, and animation.\n\n## Common Frame Rates\n\n- **24 fps**: Cinema standard\n- **25 fps**: PAL television\n- **29.97 fps**: NTSC television (drop-frame timecode)\n- **30 fps**: NTSC simplified / web video\n- **48 fps**: High frame rate cinema (HFR)\n- **50 fps**: PAL high-quality\n- **59.94 fps**: NTSC high-quality\n- **60 fps**: Games, smooth animation\n- **120 fps**: High-end displays, VR\n- **144/240/360 fps**: Gaming monitors\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,32],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[82,1]},"title":"eqFPS"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[83,1]},"title":"ordFPS"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,42],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[85,1]},"title":"showFPS"}],"comments":"Frames per second [1, 240]\n\nBounded by construction. Invalid FPS cannot exist.\n- Minimum: 1 fps (one frame per second)\n- Maximum: 240 fps (practical display limit)\n\nFrames are atomic units — you cannot have a fractional frame.\nFPS represents how many complete frames render per second.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[80,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[80,1]},"title":"FPS"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create FPS, clamping to valid range [1, 240].\n\nHandles special values:\n- **+Infinity** → 240 (maximum, \"as fast as possible\")\n- **-Infinity** → 1 (minimum, \"as slow as possible\")\n- **NaN** → 1 (invalid input, safe fallback)\n\nFor explicit rejection of invalid values, use `safeFps`.\n\n```purescript\nfps 60.0         -- FPS 60.0\nfps 0.0          -- FPS 1.0 (clamped to minimum)\nfps (-24.0)      -- FPS 1.0 (clamped to minimum)\nfps 1000.0       -- FPS 240.0 (clamped to maximum)\nfps (1.0 / 0.0)  -- FPS 240.0 (+Infinity → maximum)\nfps ((-1.0)/0.0) -- FPS 1.0 (-Infinity → minimum)\nfps (0.0 / 0.0)  -- FPS 1.0 (NaN → minimum)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[110,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[110,1]},"title":"fps"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create FPS with explicit validation, rejecting invalid values.\n\nReturns Nothing for NaN, Infinity, or values outside [1, 240].\nThis is the **secure** constructor — use it at system boundaries.\n\n```purescript\nsafeFps 60.0         -- Just (FPS 60.0)\nsafeFps 0.0          -- Nothing (below minimum)\nsafeFps (-24.0)      -- Nothing (negative)\nsafeFps (1.0 / 0.0)  -- Nothing (Infinity rejected)\nsafeFps (0.0 / 0.0)  -- Nothing (NaN rejected)\nsafeFps 1000.0       -- Nothing (exceeds maximum)\n```\n\n## Security Model\n\nNaN and Infinity are attack vectors. A malicious actor crafting\n`0.0 / 0.0` or `1.0 / 0.0` can bypass naive bounds checks.\nThis function explicitly rejects these values at the boundary.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[138,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[138,1]},"title":"safeFps"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create FPS without bounds checking\n\nUse only when you know the value is positive.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[148,27],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[148,1]},"title":"unsafeFPS"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract raw Number from FPS\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[156,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[156,1]},"title":"unwrap"},{"children":[],"comments":"Alias for unwrap\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[160,26],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[160,1]},"title":"toNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Duration of a single frame in seconds\n\n```purescript\nframeDuration (fps 60.0)  -- 0.01666... (16.67ms per frame)\nframeDuration (fps 24.0)  -- 0.04166... (41.67ms per frame)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[173,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/FPS.purs","start":[173,1]},"title":"frameDuration"},{"children":[],"comments":"Number of frames in one minute\n\n```purescript\nframesPerMinute (fps 24.0)  -- 1440\nframesPerMinute (fps 60.0)  -- 3600\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","FPS"],"FPS"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"]